description: Beautiful, recently converted East Side Brownstone. Originally built in 1890, this home went through full renovation in 2016 including new electrical, plumbing, HVAC, floors, as well as a new kitchen. No detail was spared whether it be the white oak hardwood floors, custom shades, high end light fixtures, and numerous skylights. The open concept kitchen boasts quartz counter tops, new S/S appliances alongside custom cabinets, vaulted ceilings & central A/C. Similarly, the spacious master suite with walk in closet has a full bath with heated floors, beautiful tile work and features elegant Hansgrohe fixtures. The guest bath features custom fabric wall, fabulous tile and floating vanity. Lastly, the property includes a private front and rear entrances, exclusive stair access to the roof, shared patio space, and private storage room in the basement. Not to mention you are two blocks from the beach and moments away from everything South Boston has to offer!
